I think this is a notable book. Is my judgement worse than yours? There is only one novel Uncorrected Proof dealing with uncorrected proofs. Thus it is a legitimate entry. + Different from galleys.
uncorrected proof, galleys, advance reading copies, are all publishing terms - used for different purposes
I don't see why not have both Uncorrected Proof and Galleys - they are different terms in publishing. See eg: http://lopezbooks.com/catalog/pr/pr-02.html
